# Laplace Transform as a CLM on Schwartz Space

Constructs the one-sided Laplace evaluation functional
  `L_ŌČ(h) = ‚ąę‚āÄ^‚ąě h(t) e^{-ŌČt} dt`
as a CLM `ūĚďĘ(‚ĄĚ) ‚ÜíL[‚ĄĚ] ‚ĄĚ` for `ŌČ > 0`, and proves a uniform Schwartz
seminorm bound for `ŌČ ‚Č• mass > 0`.

## Main definitions

- `schwartzLaplaceEvalCLM ŌČ hŌČ` ‚ÄĒ the Laplace evaluation CLM

## Main results

- `schwartzLaplaceEvalCLM_apply` ‚ÄĒ specification: equals the one-sided integral
- `schwartzLaplace_uniformBound` ‚ÄĒ `|L_ŌČ(h)| ‚Č§ C ¬∑ p(h)` uniformly in ŌČ ‚Č• mass

## Proof strategy

The key bound is ŌČ-independent: for h ‚ąą ūĚďĘ(‚ĄĚ) and ŌČ > 0,

  `|L_ŌČ(h)| ‚Č§ ‚ąę‚āÄ^‚ąě |h(t)| dt ‚Č§ ‚ąę‚āÄ^‚ąě p_{2,0}(h)/(1+t)¬≤ dt = p_{2,0}(h)`

since `|h(t)| ‚Č§ p_{2,0}(h) / (1+|t|)¬≤` and `‚ąę‚āÄ^‚ąě (1+t)‚ĀĽ¬≤ dt = 1`.

## References

- Reed-Simon II, ¬ßIX.3 (Schwartz space properties)
-/

